=== EMAIL ROUTER - INTEGRATED DEVELOPMENT ROADMAP ===
============================================================

### Phase: Define user stories for the Email Router:
1. As a user, I want to be able to set up forwarding rules for incoming emails to be automatically routed to specific email addresses or folders.
2. As a user, I want the ability to block or filter out certain senders or keywords in incoming emails to prevent unwanted communication.
3. As a user, I want to easily categorize incoming emails into different folders or labels based on predefined criteria.
4. As a user, I want the option to schedule emails to be routed at specific times or intervals.
5. As a user, I want to be able to set up multiple email aliases or identities for outgoing emails with the ability to choose the sender address for each message.

### Phase: Create a persona for the user interacting with the Email Router.
As a Customer Support Representative at our organization, I want to efficiently manage incoming email inquiries, so I can focus on resolving complex issues and providing high-quality customer service.

### Phase: Identify actions that the user can perform using the Email Router.
As a Customer Support Representative, I want to view incoming emails categorized by intent and urgency so that I can prioritize my responses effectively.

As an SME (Subject Matter Expert), I want to receive only relevant, complex inquiries routed to me based on content analysis so that I can focus on specialized tasks.

As an IT Administrator, I want to monitor system performance metrics and configure routing rules to ensure smooth operation of the Email Router.

As a user, I want to manually review and approve automated responses generated by the system to maintain communication quality and accuracy.

### Phase: Define the desired outcome for each user story.
Feature Name: User Profile Management
Description: This feature allows users to update their profile information, including personal details, preferences, and communication settings.
Key Functionality: Users can edit their name, email address, password, notification settings, and profile picture.
User Benefit: Provides users with the ability to customize their account details to personalize their experience and receive relevant notifications.

Feature Name: Search Functionality
Description: This feature enables users to search for specific items or content within the platform.
Key Functionality: Users can enter keywords or filters to find relevant information quickly and efficiently.
User Benefit: Helps users easily locate desired items or content, saving time and improving overall user experience.

Feature Name: In-App Messaging
Description: This feature allows users to communicate with each other directly within the application.
Key Functionality: Users can send text messages, images, and files to other users in real-time.
User Benefit: Facilitates seamless communication and collaboration between users, enhancing engagement and interaction within the platform.

### Phase: Group related user stories into features for the Email Router:
Feature 1: Email Forwarding
- Feature Name: Email Forwarding
- Description: This feature allows users to forward emails to other recipients.
- Key Functionality: Capability to forward received emails to another email address. Ability to set up rules for automatic forwarding of emails.
- User Benefit: Users can easily share important information or relevant emails with others, ensuring efficient communication and collaboration.

Feature 2: Email Filtering
- Feature Name: Email Filtering
- Description: This feature enables users to filter incoming emails based on specific criteria.
- Key Functionality: Ability to set up filters to automatically categorize emails based on sender, subject, keywords, or other criteria. Organizing emails into folders based on filtering rules.
- User Benefit: Users can prioritize and manage incoming emails more effectively, reducing clutter and enabling quicker access to important messages.

Feature 3: Email Scheduling
- Feature Name: Email Scheduling
- Description: This feature allows users to schedule emails to be sent at a later time.
- Key Functionality: Capability to compose emails and schedule them for sending at a specified date and time. Ability to delay sending an email for a specific period of time.
- User Benefit: Users can plan their communications in advance, ensuring timely delivery of messages and facilitating better time management.

Feature 4: Email Templates
- Feature Name: Email Templates
- Description: This feature enables users to save email templates for repetitive messages.
- Key Functionality: Ability to create, save, and reuse predefined email templates for common messages. Easily insert variables into email templates for personalized messages.
- User Benefit: Users can save time on composing recurring messages, maintain consistency in communication, and personalize emails efficiently.

Feature 5: Email Tracking
- Feature Name: Email Tracking
- Description: This feature allows users to track the status of their sent emails.
- Key Functionality: Capability to monitor when emails are opened by recipients and receive notifications for recipient interactions. Track email delivery status and engagement metrics.
- User Benefit: Users can gauge the effectiveness of their communications, follow up promptly when needed, and stay informed about recipient engagement with their emails.

### Phase: Segregate user stories into features like email filtering, forwarding, auto-response, etc.
Based on the user stories provided, we can organize them into the following features for the product:

1. Email Filtering Feature:
- User story: As a user, I want to filter my incoming emails based on specific criteria.
- User story: As a user, I want to set up rules to automatically categorize incoming emails into folders.

2. Email Forwarding Feature:
- User story: As a user, I want to easily forward important emails to colleagues or external contacts.
- User story: As a user, I want to set up email forwarding rules for certain types of emails.

3. Auto-Response Feature:
- User story: As a user, I want to set up automatic replies for when I am out of the office.
- User story: As a user, I want to create customized auto-response messages for different scenarios.

### Phase: Outline engineering tasks for each user story:
1. User Story: As a user, I want to be able to create a new account on the platform.

Engineering Tasks:
- Design the user interface for the account creation form.
- Implement backend logic to handle account creation requests.
- Implement frontend validation for user input.
- Write automated tests to verify account creation functionality.

2. User Story: As a user, I want to be able to search for products on the platform.

Engineering Tasks:
- Design the search bar UI component.
- Implement frontend logic to handle search queries.
- Develop backend API endpoints to handle search requests.
- Integrate search functionality with the existing product database.
- Write unit tests to ensure search functionality works as expected.

3. User Story: As a user, I want to be able to add products to my shopping cart.

Engineering Tasks:
- Design the shopping cart UI component.
- Implement frontend logic to add products to the cart.
- Update the backend to store cart information for each user.
- Implement functionalities to update and remove products from the cart.
- Write integration tests to verify the shopping cart functionality.

4. User Story: As a user, I want to be able to make a payment for my order.

Engineering Tasks:
- Design the payment form UI.
- Integrate a third-party payment gateway for processing payments.
- Implement frontend logic to handle payment submission.
- Update the backend to process payment requests and update order status.
- Write end-to-end tests to verify the payment process from start to finish.

